data.title: Amazon reported Q3 FY2025 earnings: $180.2B revenue, $17.4B operating income. AWS growing 20.2% YoY, backlog at $200B. Stores innovating for customers with expanded selection, prices, and faster delivery. Ads revenue $17.6B, 22% growth YoY.
data.description: Amazon.com, Inc. released its third-quarter 2025 earnings report showing $180.2 billion in revenue, a 12% increase year over year (excluding foreign exchange impact). The operating income was $17.4 billion, which could have been over $21 billion if not for two special expenses. Amazon Web Services (AWS) saw significant growth, with a 20.2% year-over-year increase, reaching a backlog of $200 billion by the end of the quarter. AWS is gaining momentum in core and AI workloads due to its functionality and performance. The company continues to innovate in AI, launching new features like Amazon Bedrock and Amazon Curo. The Stores division also showed innovation and growth, offering more selection, low prices, and convenience, including fast delivery options. Amazon's advertising business generated $17.6 billion in revenue, growing 22% year over year, with partnerships with companies like Netflix, Spotify, and Sirius XM. The company is investing heavily in capacity expansion to meet growing customer demand.

data.title: Black Diamond increases dividend after reporting Q3 2025 results. Provider of space rental and workforce solutions.
data.description: On October 30, 2025, in Calgary, Alberta, Black Diamond Group Limited disclosed its operational and financial outcomes for the three and nine months concluding on September 30, 2025. data.title: ANSI releases Oct. 2025 Gaps Progress Report for EV standards to boost safe adoption nationwide.
data.description: In a move to promote the safe and extensive use of electric vehicles (EVs) and their infrastructure throughout the country, the American National Standards Institute (ANSI) unveiled the October 2025 Gaps Progress Report in New York on October 30th, 2025. The report provides crucial updates on the gaps currently present in the EV industry.

data.title: Atlassian Corp's Q1 revenue exceeds estimates at $1.43B, with adjusted earnings at $1.04/share. Cloud revenue grew by 26%.
data.description: Atlassian Corp (NASDAQ: TEAM) released their first quarter fiscal 2026 financial results, exceeding expectations and presenting strong numbers. The company reported $1.43 billion in revenue for Q1, surpassing analyst projections of $1.40 billion. Their adjusted earnings for the quarter were $1.04 per share, higher than the anticipated 84 cents per share. Atlassian saw a 21% year-over-year increase in total revenue, with Cloud revenue specifically growing by 26%. In terms of cash flow, they generated $129 million. This positive performance has positioned Atlassian among the top performers for the day. For more detailed insights, analysts recommend checking out further analysis on the matter.

data.title: Rosewood Hong Kong tops list of world's best hotels 2025 in London ceremony with 20 Asian hotels in top 50.
data.description: The prestigious announcement of the world's best hotels for 2025 included properties from 22 different destinations spanning six continents. data.description: In San Diego on October 30, 2025, Compass Dermatopathology is pleased to reveal that its leader, Antoanella Calame, MD, a certified dermatologist and dermatopathologist, has been recognized as one of the "Top Doctors" in Dermatopathology for the year 2025.

data.title: Timberland Bancorp's 2025 fiscal year net income increased to $29.16 million EPS rose to $3.67. A new branch in University Place announced.
data.description: Timberland Bancorp, Inc. reported strong financial results with net income increasing 20% to $29.16 million for the fiscal year ended September 30, 2025. Earnings per diluted common share ("EPS") increased by 22% to $3.67. Quarterly EPS increased by 19% to $1.07. Quarterly net interest margin increased to 3.82%, Return on Average Assets to 1.68%, and Return on Average Equity to 12.97%. The company announced an 8% increase in the quarterly cash dividend to $0.28 per share and plans to open a branch in University Place. Total assets reached $2.0 billion with a 3% increase, while total deposits increased by 3% and shareholders' equity increased by 2%. Non-performing assets to total assets ratio was 0.23%. Timberland originated $100.09 million in loans during the quarter. Total deposits increased by $47.16 million to $1.72 billion. Total shareholders' equity increased by 2% to $262.61 million. The company remains well capitalized with a total risk-based capital ratio of 20.67% and a Tier 1 leverage capital ratio of 12.59%.

data.title: Buenaventura announces Q3 & 9M 2025 results, Peru's largest metals mining company. Figures in USD, prepared under IFRS.
data.description: Peru's largest publicly-traded precious metals mining company, Compañia de Minas Buenaventura S.A.A., released its financial results for the third quarter and nine-month period ending on September 30, 2025. The figures, reported in U.S. dollars (US$) and prepared according to International Financial Reporting Standards (IFRS) on a non-GAAP basis, show the company's performance during 3Q25 and 9M25. Buenaventura is listed on the New York Stock Exchange under the ticker symbol BVN and on the Lima Stock Exchange under BUE.LM.

data.title: ThreeD Capital Inc renews investor relations agreement with PHK Investments LLC, paying £6,875/month and £20,000/month in ad spend. Also issues 100,000 stock options at $0.40/share.
data.description: ThreeD Capital Inc. has extended its agreement with PHK Investments LLC to provide investor relations services, replacing the previous arrangement that expired on October 8, 2025. Under the new Agreement, ThreeD will pay a fixed monthly fee of £6,875 (approximately $12,640 CAD) and up to £20,000 (approximately $36,772 CAD) in monthly ad spend. The Company will also issue 100,000 stock options exercisable at $0.40 per share. Half of the options vest in six months and the rest in 12 months, expiring two years from the grant date if unexercised.
